@AgDude 
This is not a good idea. If a client WS connection broke and then reconnects, the client fetches the old message. Therefore the persistence feature of Redis is really useful.
On the other hand, if a client sends upstream, the Django-loop has to collect that data sometimes, asynchronously. This only works with persisted messages.

